description:
Subjects Addressed:
(1) While probation was drawing to a close in Christ’s day, the Jewish leaders were plotting to kill Christ
(2) Today, as probation is about to close, religious leaders, in Babylon and in SDA church are not only planning but are crucifying/denouncing present-truth
(3) Catholicism softens stance on homosexuality and divorce, as was prophesied in The Great Controversy, page 565
(4) Papacy pacifies her tone to appear tolerant; while her objective is to regain world dominance, persecute dissenters, and undo all that Protestantism has done
(5) Papacy adapts itself to appeal to all classes, by appealing to those who would be saved by their merits, and those who would be saved in their sins. Here is the secret of its power.
(6) Among many SDA church leaders, tradition is placed above scripture in voting to ordain women as pastors and/or elders. The NAD states it will continue to ordain women as elders regardless of the vote.
(7) Elder Ted Wilson states that truth is being crucified among SDAs because of the promotion and tolerance of apostasy by leaders in our churches, schools, and other institutions
(8) If SDA church vote to allow unbiblical practices, GC 595 and AA 68 tell us how to respond.  
(9) Whenever the gospel, the Three Angels’ Message, is preached worldwide, this account of Mary anointing Jesus should be connected
(10) Christ’s body, His church, must be anointed before the close of probation
(11) Mary gave all because she was completely delivered and received complete victory (seven times), so must we give all
(12) We are to anoint Jesus’ feet as Mary did by giving all—time, means, attention, exertion, mental strength, physical strength, etc. to the proclamation of the gospel
(13) Church members will accuse and criticize your efforts to anoint Christ and give all to Him and the proclamation of the gospel, and call it a waste, but Christ will receive our worship

Website: www.prophesyagain.org
